rComments: Pat's dedication to bringing social justice issues into the classroom is refreshing. She designs her lectures so that there is lots of hands-on work and collaboration. She is also very engaged with what her students are thinking and feeling and makes the classroom feel like a shared space. There really is not enough room here for me to say enough.

Pat is a revolutionary both in and out of the field of education. Her dedication to bringing social justice issues to the forefront is refreshing. Her democratic teaching style is one that more teachers need to embrace. She is visionary in her approach and students who do not see that are missing out on what it means to redefine education.

I highly appreciate all what I learned in Pat's classes. She provides a lot of relevant readings and open the space for discussions in class. I liked her democratic style in teaching.  look forward to take my second course with her in the summer though it is Ramadan but I do want to learn more from her. Appreciate it Pat!

I have so much respect for Pat and I highly recommend her courses.  She has a unique teaching style and really knows her stuff!  She also brings her passions into the classroom and always encourages her students to do the same. I look forward to my third course with Pat this summer. :)

She is the best ever. She is very flixable. She calls for justice in educational rights in everywhere. This is my first course with her and if I would have the chance to register for her next courses I will not hesitate.
One of the best Ottawa has to offer. Pat is one of those profs who pushes, who supports, and who brings out the best in her students. Highly recommend.

Taking her class is a life changing experience, in the best sense.  Excellent teaching style and completely open to students interests.  She has a unique background and worldview and is extremely interesting to listen to, so sit back and enjoy!
